00:14:35.958 --> 00:14:37.585
Thanks for the insight. genius.

256
00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:38.753
I was...

257
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:41.798
I was trying to be nice.

258
00:14:41.881 --> 00:14:42.882
Well. you failed.

259
00:14:44.133 --> 00:14:45.134
Well. fuck you.

260
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.642
Dude. seriously.

261
00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:55.728
What's the point of even
attempting with that girl?

262
00:14:55.937 --> 00:14:57.647
Yeah. been there. forgot that.

263
00:14:58.106 --> 00:15:00.066
Don't you need every vote. Marcus?

264
00:15:00.149 --> 00:15:01.275
I don't need that one!

265
00:15:01.359 --> 00:15:03.069
Guys. leave Zach alone.

266
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:07.156
He's just desperate to lose it before
his dad has to buy him a hooker.

267
00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:08.449
[all laugh]

268
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:10.201
You get back here. young man!

269
00:15:10.284 --> 00:15:11.285
Zachy!

270
00:15:11.369 --> 00:15:12.370
Poor Zach!

271
00:15:12.453 --> 00:15:13.454
Yo. Zachy!

272
00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:16.082
[Hannah]
<i>You said something stupid. Zach...

273
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:17.542
<i>and I yelled at you.

274
00:15:18.167 --> 00:15:19.168
<i>Big deal.

275
00:15:22.422 --> 00:15:23.673
<i>You should have let it go.

276
00:15:25.216 --> 00:15:26.342
<i>But you didn't let it go.

277
00:15:27.802 --> 00:15:29.887
<i>You didn't like that someone told you no.

278
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:33.391
<i>'Cause guys like you</i>
<i>get anything you want. right?

279
00:15:39.021 --> 00:15:40.273
[Matt] You're home early.

280
00:15:44.193 --> 00:15:45.027
Hey.

281
00:15:45.611 --> 00:15:47.071
Come sit with me a minute.

282
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:02.879
This isn't a talk. is it?

283
00:16:03.337 --> 00:16:04.589
No talk.

284
00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:07.508
We'll communicate through semaphores.

285
00:16:09.218 --> 00:16:12.597
I can see how you'd think I'd be the
one person to laugh at that. but...

286
00:16:13.848 --> 00:16:14.849
Where's your bike?

287
00:16:17.018 --> 00:16:18.019
Uh...

288
00:16:18.519 --> 00:16:21.022
I uh... messed up the crank...

289
00:16:21.856 --> 00:16:23.941
so I left it with Tony. to fix it.

290
00:16:27.320 --> 00:16:28.237
Listen.

291
00:16:29.530 --> 00:16:31.365
About what you heard this morning.

292
00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:32.867
I didn't hear anything.

293
00:16:33.367 --> 00:16:35.536
Well. if you did...

294
00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:38.206
your mom and I...

295
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:42.418
we disagree on some things.

296
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:44.378
I didn't hear anything. Dad.

297
00:16:45.630 --> 00:16:46.506
Honest.

298
00:16:47.173 --> 00:16:49.175
She thinks maybe you're having
nightmares again.

299
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:55.848
And if you are...

300
00:16:56.557 --> 00:16:58.643
and if you want
to talk to someone about them.

301
00:16:58.726 --> 00:17:00.895
someone who doesn't share your DNA...

302
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:02.980
I'll... I'll let you know.

303
00:17:07.652 --> 00:17:09.695
Look. I hated high school.

304
00:17:11.113 --> 00:17:12.490
I couldn't wait to get out.

305
00:17:13.241 --> 00:17:15.034
It was hell for me.

306
00:17:17.453 --> 00:17:18.579
I was a target...

307
00:17:20.122 --> 00:17:21.541
more than once.

308
00:17:24.001 --> 00:17:24.877
Shit.

309
00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:26.671
I'm sorry. Dad.

310
00:17:27.088 --> 00:17:28.089
But I survived.

311
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:30.883
And look at me now.

312
00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:32.885
I'm a paragon of manhood.

313
00:17:34.971 --> 00:17:36.806
With a fucking beautiful family.

314
00:17:40.017 --> 00:17:40.851
Yeah.

315
00:17:41.686 --> 00:17:42.728
You did all right.

316
00:17:44.772 --> 00:17:45.940
What I'm saying...

317
00:17:47.233 --> 00:17:48.526
I had things to hang on to.

318
00:17:48.609 --> 00:17:49.986
I had chess club.

319
00:17:50.069 --> 00:17:51.070
I had Knowledge Bowl--

320
00:17:51.153 --> 00:17:52.905
See. now you're
embarrassing yourself. Dad.

321
00:17:53.406 --> 00:17:54.615
Do you have something?

322
00:17:55.575 --> 00:17:57.994
Does anything bring you joy?

323
00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:00.871
Or just relief?

324
00:18:03.583 --> 00:18:06.711
Your mom and I would feel
so much better if you had something...

325
00:18:08.963 --> 00:18:11.382
if you took more of an interest in.
you know...

326
00:18:12.174 --> 00:18:13.676
school activities.

327
00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:16.637
You know...

328
00:18:18.389 --> 00:18:20.975
I was actually thinking of going
to the basketball game tonight...

329
00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:22.643
believe it or not.

330
00:18:24.228 --> 00:18:25.313
I have. uh...

331
00:18:27.064 --> 00:18:28.024
a friend playing.

332
00:18:41.621 --> 00:18:43.956
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you think you deserve</i>
<i>everything you get...

333
00:18:45.249 --> 00:18:46.250
<i>and more.

334
00:18:47.293 --> 00:18:49.795
<i>Maybe you're just used to hearing</i>
<i>the cheers of the crowd.

335
00:18:51.088 --> 00:18:52.465
[crowd cheering]

336
00:19:09.190 --> 00:19:10.149
Clay.

337
00:19:11.359 --> 00:19:12.485
What are you doing here?

338
00:19:13.277 --> 00:19:15.655
It's a basketball game.
I'm here to show some school spirit.

339
00:19:16.906 --> 00:19:17.782
That's great.

340
00:19:18.199 --> 00:19:19.158
Great. Clay.

341
00:19:19.575 --> 00:19:20.826
I'm glad you're. you know...

342
00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:22.995
feeling better.

343
00:19:23.245 --> 00:19:24.163
Hey.

344
00:19:25.456 --> 00:19:26.332
How's it going?

345
00:19:27.208 --> 00:19:28.751
Everything's great. Marcus.

346
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:31.212
What the fuck are you doing here. dude?

347
00:19:31.295 --> 00:19:32.421
What's your play now?

348
00:19:33.214 --> 00:19:34.215
[Tyler] Hey. guys.

349
00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:36.133
Can I get a picture?

350
00:19:36.509 --> 00:19:38.511
Nothing's going on. Tyler. Just go away.

351
00:19:38.594 --> 00:19:40.805
I seriously just wanted
a picture for the yearbook.

352
00:19:41.013 --> 00:19:43.099
If they knew the kind of pictures
you really took!

353
00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:44.183
[Mr. Porter] Hey.

354
00:19:44.266 --> 00:19:45.976
These T-shirts look great.

355
00:19:46.477 --> 00:19:48.354
Uh. I'm glad you approve. Mr. Porter.

356
00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:51.065
I appreciate all the hard work
you guys put into it.

357
00:19:51.315 --> 00:19:52.400
[Marcus] Mr. Down...

358
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.985
would you get a picture of us
for the yearbook?

359
00:19:56.070 --> 00:19:57.071
Yeah.

360
00:19:57.905 --> 00:19:58.739
Yeah.

361
00:19:58.823 --> 00:20:00.074
[clock buzzes]

362
00:20:00.157 --> 00:20:01.450
[audience cheers]

363
00:20:04.787 --> 00:20:05.788
[whistle blows]

364
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:19.093
Clay. what are you doing?
Get off the court.

365
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.303
Jensen. get off the fucking court.

366
00:20:21.387 --> 00:20:22.638
[audience booing]

367
00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:25.516
What the hell. Jensen?

368
00:20:25.599 --> 00:20:26.851
Game's about to start.

369
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:30.438
-[whistle blows]
-[crowd erupts]

370
00:20:30.521 --> 00:20:32.523
Hey. you! Get off the court!

371
00:20:35.067 --> 00:20:35.943
[whistle continues]

372
00:20:36.026 --> 00:20:37.528
Get off the court. Go.

373
00:20:37.611 --> 00:20:39.405
Hey. skinny kid.
get the hell off the court.

374
00:20:44.535 --> 00:20:45.953
Clay. you okay?

375
00:20:47.288 --> 00:20:48.330
Do you care?

376
00:20:52.084 --> 00:20:53.461
Where the hell's Jessica?

377
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:55.254
She texted me.

378
00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:57.173
She was babysitting her brothers

379
00:20:57.256 --> 00:20:59.467
and had to wait
till her mom got home to leave.

380
00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:01.802
Well. we can't wait for her.

381
00:21:02.344 --> 00:21:04.722
Okay. ladies. let's go!

382
00:21:04.805 --> 00:21:06.223
[girls cheering]

383
00:21:07.266 --> 00:21:10.561
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you can't imagine what it</i>
<i>feels like to be on the sidelines. Zach...

384
00:21:11.854 --> 00:21:13.063
<i>like most of us are.

385
00:21:13.147 --> 00:21:14.190
[buzzer]

386
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:20.863
[bell rings]

387
00:21:21.572 --> 00:21:24.867
<i>You can't imagine why a little</i>
<i>piece of paper could mean so much.

388
00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:31.749
Um. everybody. before you leave.

389
00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:35.336
we've added an anonymous
class discussion bag to the racks.

390
00:21:35.419 --> 00:21:38.047
We're gonna check it every Friday
and talk it over.

391
00:21:41.509 --> 00:21:43.219
You got another bunny?

392
00:21:44.303 --> 00:21:45.596
I wish I would get one.

393
00:21:45.679 --> 00:21:47.014
Still don't know who they're from?

394
00:21:51.602 --> 00:21:53.437
You got. like. six compliments today.

395
00:21:53.687 --> 00:21:56.524
I got a cartoon
and a campaign flyer from Courtney.

396
00:21:56.607 --> 00:21:57.691
Yeah.

397
00:21:58.567 --> 00:22:01.612
You do realize shilling for votes
is not a compliment. Courtney.

398
00:22:02.613 --> 00:22:04.114
I'm sorry you feel that way. Skye.

399
00:22:04.198 --> 00:22:07.451
but I'm proud of my efforts.
and I wanted to share that with the class.

400
00:22:09.245 --> 00:22:10.454
[laughing]

401
00:22:20.923 --> 00:22:22.341
[crowd cheering]

402
00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:26.845
[Tyler] Hey. Clay.

403
00:22:28.389 --> 00:22:29.682
Go away. Tyler.

404
00:22:30.432 --> 00:22:31.976
You know. I get that a lot.

405
00:22:32.393 --> 00:22:34.186
Especially lately. But today I'm on...

406
00:22:35.020 --> 00:22:37.439
official yearbook business.

407
00:22:40.943 --> 00:22:42.444
Why are you even talking to me?

408
00:22:43.737 --> 00:22:45.614
Because I want to see
what you're gonna do next.

409
00:22:46.198 --> 00:22:48.701
You really messed Courtney up.
Not as much as you did to me.

410
00:22:49.410 --> 00:22:50.411
Still...

411
00:22:51.120 --> 00:22:52.246
the cemetery?

412
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:53.706
That's cold.

413
00:22:56.041 --> 00:22:57.585
Does everybody know about that?

414
00:22:58.502 --> 00:23:00.337
Everybody knows about everything.

415
00:23:00.796 --> 00:23:02.172
They know about your nightmares.

416
00:23:02.256 --> 00:23:04.174
They know you beat off
to Hannah's picture.

417
00:23:04.675 --> 00:23:06.176
And they know what you did to her.

418
00:23:09.263 --> 00:23:10.264
What is it?

419
00:23:11.682 --> 00:23:12.850
What did I do?

420
00:23:14.727 --> 00:23:15.728
What?

421
00:23:18.897 --> 00:23:19.898
Clay?

422
00:23:23.611 --> 00:23:24.612
Heads up.

423
00:23:29.074 --> 00:23:30.826
Jensen. come on. throw the damn ball.

424
00:23:32.286 --> 00:23:33.287
Clay.

425
00:23:33.370 --> 00:23:34.538
[heart beating]

426
00:23:35.497 --> 00:23:37.041
-Clay.
-[player] Come on!

427
00:23:37.374 --> 00:23:39.376
Come on. what are you waiting for?

428
00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:41.670
Throw the ball. dipshit.

429
00:23:43.672 --> 00:23:45.382
Jesus. Clay. what the fuck?

430
00:23:47.509 --> 00:23:48.510
[Tyler] Clay.

431
00:23:50.179 --> 00:23:51.013
Clay.

432
00:23:52.306 --> 00:23:54.350
-Clay.
-[player] We got a game. man!

433
00:23:54.516 --> 00:23:56.143
Throw it in. loser!

434
00:23:57.519 --> 00:23:58.646
[crowd laughing]

435
00:23:59.438 --> 00:24:00.814
Thanks for making me do that.

436
00:24:01.023 --> 00:24:02.107
[whistle blows]

437
00:24:07.321 --> 00:24:08.530
Uh-uh. No way.

438
00:24:09.073 --> 00:24:10.991
You've been late to practice
twice this week.

439
00:24:11.283 --> 00:24:13.285
Now you miss most of first quarter?

440
00:24:13.535 --> 00:24:15.704
I'm sorry.
I didn't know I was going to be so late.

441
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:18.540
Jess. look. you got a problem.

442
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:20.376
come to me. we'll work it out.

443
00:24:20.834 --> 00:24:23.212
But I'm sorry. you're out of today's game.

444
00:24:23.379 --> 00:24:24.463
[buzzer]

445
00:24:35.224 --> 00:24:36.392
[Bryce] Yo. Jess.

446
00:24:36.517 --> 00:24:37.643
You're not leaving. are you?

447
00:24:37.726 --> 00:24:39.228
I'm benched for the game.

448
00:24:39.478 --> 00:24:41.772
Or didn't the entire gym just hear that?

449
00:24:41.980 --> 00:24:43.440
Well. if you're benched. take a seat.

450
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:45.609
-Make some room. you guys.
-[Jess] I don't know.

451
00:24:46.443 --> 00:24:48.862
Come on. you don't want to miss
your boyfriend's big game.

452
00:24:49.571 --> 00:24:50.572
And...

453
00:24:50.864 --> 00:24:52.324
we're having fun up there.

454
00:24:59.999 --> 00:25:01.208
[Bryce] Milady.

455
00:25:01.291 --> 00:25:04.253
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you don't know what</i>
<i>it's like to need a lifeline. Zach.

456
00:25:05.170 --> 00:25:06.171
[bell rings]

457
00:25:14.096 --> 00:25:16.724
<i>The day after you insulted me</i>
<i>in the cafeteria.

458
00:25:16.807 --> 00:25:18.726
<i>my compliment bag was empty.

459
00:25:21.228 --> 00:25:22.604
<i>Not even a cute bunny.

460
00:25:23.480 --> 00:25:24.440
[bell rings]

461
00:25:25.107 --> 00:25:27.359
<i>By the end of the second week.</i>
<i>I knew something was up.

462
00:25:36.076 --> 00:25:38.620
<i>Maybe I should have let it go.</i>
<i>but I didn't.

463
00:25:39.455 --> 00:25:40.706
<i>I wrote you a letter.

464
00:25:41.206 --> 00:25:42.624
<i>I poured my heart out.

465
00:25:42.708 --> 00:25:44.585
<i>opening up about personal things

466
00:25:44.668 --> 00:25:46.837
<i>I hadn't had the courage</i>
<i>to admit to anyone:

467
00:25:47.087 --> 00:25:48.922
<i>How hard life was getting...

468
00:25:49.465 --> 00:25:50.924
<i>how lonely I felt...

469
00:25:51.383 --> 00:25:54.553
<i>and how those stupid compliments</i>
<i>actually meant something to me.

470
00:26:04.062 --> 00:26:05.272
<i>And then I set my trap.

471
00:26:19.578 --> 00:26:21.038
[bell rings]

472
00:26:56.615 --> 00:26:59.243
<i>I was hoping once you read</i>
<i>the letter. you'd get it.

473
00:26:59.326 --> 00:27:02.663
<i>you'd realize how much I needed those</i>
<i>silly things you were stealing from me.

474
00:27:06.708 --> 00:27:08.794
<i>But I guess I wasn't even</i>
<i>worth a reaction.

475
00:27:13.215 --> 00:27:14.299
Why me. Zach?

476
00:27:15.759 --> 00:27:16.844
Why me?

477
00:27:27.312 --> 00:27:28.397
[cheering]

478
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:32.192
Wow. that's double digits already.

479
00:27:38.949 --> 00:27:39.992
[crowd cheers]

480
00:27:54.298 --> 00:27:55.299
Jeez.

481
00:27:55.382 --> 00:27:57.217
Zach is on fire tonight.

482
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:03.223
Whoo!

483
00:28:05.183 --> 00:28:07.519
[chanting] Zach! Zach! Zach! Zach!

484
00:28:20.073 --> 00:28:21.408
[chanting continues] Zach! Zach!

485
00:28:24.494 --> 00:28:28.790
Oh-ho-ho-ho! Yeah!

486
00:28:39.176 --> 00:28:40.177
Stop it!

487
00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:41.345
Stop! Stop it!

488
00:28:41.428 --> 00:28:43.055
Stop playing! Stop the game! Stop!

489
00:28:43.263 --> 00:28:44.932
Stop it! Stop. stop!

490
00:28:54.316 --> 00:28:55.609
[student] Is he crazy?

491
00:29:09.623 --> 00:29:10.874
[Hannah] <i>Why me. Zach?

492
00:29:11.500 --> 00:29:12.709
<i>Why me?

493
00:29:31.186 --> 00:29:32.396
[scraping]

494
00:29:41.363 --> 00:29:42.948
[Skye] Stickin' it to the man!

495
00:29:44.074 --> 00:29:47.452
Or. you know. one particular man
who's rich enough and fucked-up enough

496
00:29:47.536 --> 00:29:49.830
to get his asshole son a $60.000 car.

497
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:51.957
Skye. what are you...

498
00:29:52.249 --> 00:29:53.542
Are you at the game?

499
00:29:53.959 --> 00:29:55.002
God. no!

500
00:29:57.212 --> 00:29:58.338
Sculpture studio.

501
00:29:58.714 --> 00:30:01.633
It's the only time I can get
the welding rig away from the shop boys.

502
00:30:04.344 --> 00:30:05.470
Were you at the game?

503
00:30:07.389 --> 00:30:08.390
I was.

504
00:30:09.182 --> 00:30:11.643
But it was so bad.
you had to leave before halftime?

505
00:30:15.814 --> 00:30:16.815
I can't...

506
00:30:18.734 --> 00:30:20.068
I can't do this anymore.

507
00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:22.821
This goddamn school.

508
00:30:22.904 --> 00:30:24.114
it's a terrible place.

509
00:30:24.614 --> 00:30:26.992
You're just now coming
to this realization?

510
00:30:28.201 --> 00:30:30.704
Where have you been for
the past three years?

511
00:30:32.331 --> 00:30:33.498
Oh. that's right.

512
00:30:33.582 --> 00:30:34.958
pining after a pretty dead girl.

513
00:30:37.627 --> 00:30:38.545
Why are you so mean?

514
00:30:40.339 --> 00:30:41.798
I thought we were friends.

515
00:30:43.425 --> 00:30:44.426
Were.

516
00:30:45.427 --> 00:30:46.678
We were friends.

517
00:30:48.305 --> 00:30:49.473
What happened?

518
00:30:51.016 --> 00:30:52.184
I didn't understand it.

519
00:30:52.768 --> 00:30:53.977
I still don't.

520
00:30:54.353 --> 00:30:56.271
